s. He shows how adolescent qualities have slowly seeped upwards, where they have gradually reshaped the norms and habits of adulthood. The effects over the long haul, Howe contends, have been profound, in both the private realm and in the public arena of political, economic, and social interaction. Our teenage traits remain part of us as we move into adulthood. We now need instruction manuals for adulting!Teen Spirit challenges our assumptions about the boundaries between adolescence and adulthood. Yet despite a cultural system that seems to be built on the ethos of Generation Me, it's not all bad. In fact, there is an equally impressive rise in creativity, diversity, and tolerance within society: all traits stemming from core components of the adolescent character. Howe's bold and suggestive approach to analyzing the teen in all of us helps make sense of the impulsivity driving society and to think anew about civic re-engagement.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aAdolescencexSocial aspectszUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aAdolescencexSocial aspectszUnited StatesxHistoryy21st century. 0aAdulthoodxSocial aspectszUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aAdulthoodxSocial aspectszUnited StatesxHistoryy21st century. 0aEmotional maturityzUnited States. 4aCultural Studies. 4aCurrent Events. 4aSociology & Social Science. 7aPSYCHOLOGY / Developmental / Adulthood & Aging.2bisacsh  aMillennials, Individualism, tolerance, Adolescence, Character, individualism, incivility, adulting, generation x.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCOR eBook-Package Pilot Project 2020z978311069046008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG0